<b>New tactic! - </b>5/1/01 12:04:45 AM<br>~ <b>Ensis Arament</b><blockquote>Once you recieve this song after the long hell-level known as 45, you're amply rewarded with a new tactic you can do.  In truth, you could still do it without this song, but it wouldn't be as effective.<br><br>What I'm talking about is Chant Kiting.  Run around in circles with the drum equipped and blast away a MOB with all three chants.  You'll take no damage, lose no mana, have no downtime, and kill the MOB within 4 minutes, depending on resists.  Amazing way to gain experience--Never suffer another boring day on the Karnor's Castle wall again!<br><br>Some may think that you have to twist four songs for this to work, but it isn't true.  By all means, if you CAN keep all three chants and Selo's up, then do it.  But I suggest you get yourself a 10-Shot SoW potion.  You won't move as fast, but your hands are free to twist three songs instead of four.  You'll easily make the money back and then some through this tactic.<br><br>I would have to suggest using this around the Firionia Vie zoneline in the Dreadlands.  You can get plenty of high level MOBs there, and if you're aware, nearly no adds.  Careful with the Drachnids though, since they run at SoW speed... turn on the Levitate on your Singing Steel Boots and you should keep ahead.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
